The paper deals with privacy-preserving storage protocols, which are typically studied in the cryptography (cs.CR) and data structures (cs.DS) communities. The paper also discusses key-value storage, which is a common topic in database systems (cs.DB). The use of differential privacy as a privacy notion suggests that the paper may also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC) communities.
